HEADWORD: Murex
<hw>Mu"rex</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Murices</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., the purple fish.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of marine gastropods, having rough, and
frequently spinose, shells, which are often highly colored inside; the
rock shells. They abound in tropical seas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

